### Specific species

Szuwalski et al.2020 lists a few of the major capture fisheries, which I did a quick search for on AquaMaps to get an idea of distributions. The smallest distributions I saw were the Mauxia shrimp (Acetes chinensis)and the Black scraper (Thamnaconus modestus), which each appear to range from Northern Japan to the South China Sea. I pulled data for the shrimp because it looks to be limited to shallower waters and thus have a smaller distribution.

Here I am calculating the total range area:

Total range of A. chinensis based on these data is 4.0708545^{6} km2

\[Marine\ aquaculture=2.3x{10}^6\ ha=23,000{km}^2\]

\[\therefore\ ocean\ farms = \frac{23,000\ {km}^2}{4,0000,000\ {km}^2}=0.575\%\]
